<div class="sectionBlock-section">
	<div class="sectionBlock-section-title">Introduction</div>
	<div class="sectionBlock-section-text">
		The AssetLink API can be used to manage and track legal ownership of digital assets (e-books in particular).<br />
		A single deployment of the API can be used by multiple parties including different kinds of 'digital-marketplaces' (merchants) that each have their own customers.<br />
		The customers can have their assets managed by multiple merchants of their choosing.
	</div>
</div>
<div class="sectionBlock-section">
	<div class="sectionBlock-section-title">Asset legality</div>
	<div class="sectionBlock-section-text">
		Legality of the e-books is verified by checking their official download links. These links, only known to their rightful original owners, all lead to trusted legal sources of the digital material.
		<br /><br />
		Other types of digital assets should be checked in different ways depending on their legal source.
	</div>
</div>